class Solution {
    public int binaryGap(int n) {
        int last = -1, ans = 0;
        for (int i = 0; n != 0; i++) {
            if ((n & 1) == 1) {
                if (last != -1) {
                    ans = Math.max(ans, i - last);
                }
                last = i;
            }
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the bits of the given number n from right to left, keeping track of the position of the last encountered 1. It updates the maximum distance between two adjacent 1's whenever it encounters a new 1. The iteration continues until all bits of n are processed.
